refentry:
elements primaryie primaryie Element
primaryie &primaryie.purpose;
&primaryie.synopsis.gen; Description
PrimaryIE identifies the most significant word or words in an IndexEntry. IndexEntrys occur in an Index, not in the flow of the text. They are part of a formatted index, not markers for indexing.
If a document includes both IndexTerms and IndexEntrys, the IndexEntrys are usually constructed from the IndexTerms by some external process.
Processing expectations
&format.block; The PrimaryIE starts a new entry in the Index.
&FutureChanges;
&fu.interfacedefinition;
&primaryie.parents.gen; &primaryie.children.gen;
Attributes
linkends
Linkends, if used, points to the IndexTerms indexed by this entry.
See Also &primaryie.seealso.gen;
